main event: A civilian in Medford, Mass reported a sighting of a white, cigar-shaped object of unknown nature in April 1952.
interesting points: The object was initially white in color and described as cigar-shaped.
It was reported to have exhibited high-speed and hovering maneuvers.
The conclusion was that there was insufficient data for evaluation, and the object was labeled as unknown.
The report mentioned 'sensor lint' in the comments, possibly indicating uncertainty or interference with detection equipment.
No photographs were included in the report.
